article.headline: Louisiana-Monroe beats Arkansas State 70-61
article.story: MONROE, La. -- Marvin Williams made 9 of 12 shots and finished with a career-high 22 points to lead Louisiana-Monroe past Arkansas State 70-61 on Monday night. Williams made the first basket of the game on his way to 10 first-half points as Louisiana-Monroe held a 30-24 advantage. Tylor Ongwae, Majok Deng and Justin Roberson had 10 points apiece for Louisiana-Monroe (7-6, 1-1 Sun Belt). The Warhawks made 29 of 53 shots (54.7 percent). Six straight points by Ongwae gave Louisiana-Monroe a 13-point lead, its largest of the night, with 3:03 left. Cameron Golden made four 3-pointers on his way to 25 points for Arkansas State (6-6, 1-2). P.J. Hardwick had 15 and Anthony Livingston added 10 for the Red Wolves. Three of Golden's 3-pointers came in the final six minutes of the game -- for Arkansas State's only field goals during that span.
